reviews_data.review_text: Spent a few hours visiting with a friend while enjoying an iced coffee. Staff was super friendly and efficient. Would have coffee there again.

Truthfully this place is really good. Is it expensive yes. But it is cozy and a great place to get a drink before or after a long walk. However, the customer service is so awful. They girls just look at you in the face like you’re stupid. I ask questions and they give me one word answers. I asked for a remake because the chai was awful and they just looked and said can’t. For a 9$ chai that’s ridiculous. They are just plain rude and because of that I am done with this location and will not be coming back. For a place that charges you 9$ for a chai you would think the staff would be kind. If you want good customer service, here is not the place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Kristen, thank you for sharing your feedback. We’re glad you enjoyed the space, but we’re truly sorry your experience with our service and chai didn’t meet expectations. That’s not the standard we aim for, and we have addressed this with our team. We hope you’ll consider giving us another chance in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: Parking is tough but that is because business is good. And business is good because coffee and food is excellent.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Mathew, It's wonderful to hear you enjoyed our coffee and food! We understand parking can sometimes be a challenge, and we truly appreciate you mentioning that it's due to how busy we get. Thanks for the great feedback! PRO-TIP, Ginbu the restaurant across the street allows us to use there parking lot if you leave before 11:00am when they open.

reviews_data.review_text: I just love this place. Coffee and food is always great and the atmosphere is lovely.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Megan,
Thank You so much for the incredible review. I will share this review with our staff, they will love it! We hope to see you again soon. have a great weekend!

reviews_data.review_text: A tyrant 🚓 friendly establishment that I wouldn't spend my hard earned and back breaking money at. Idk about y'all but that isn't my cup of coffee ☕

Likely the best specialty coffee Shop chains that maintain a high quality standard across multiple locations.
This specific location has an automatic espresso machine yet still providing good quality espresso with decent crema and proportions
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Negruta,
It sounds like you know a lot about coffee. Yes, we were hoping to be a busy cafe so we decided to purchase a Eversys espresso machine upon opening. We really like that it makes very good consistent espresso a bit faster than more manual machines. As I'm sure you are aware, it's more about the coffee beans then it is about the machine and we really do serve a fantastic espresso. Our Kilimanjaro, like all our our beans are roasted by the Summit Coffee Roastery just up the road in Cornelius. This allows us to control the quality and you know your always getting the freshest coffee in your cup. Thank you so much for the great review. We hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Love this place! Best espresso in town. Just wish the lighting was dimmer in the evening. Better atmosphere that way!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello, we really appreciate you sharing your experience with us. I’m glad you like the espresso, food and atmosphere. I’ll talk to the managers and baristas about putting the shades down in the afternoon. Thanks for your feedback.

reviews_data.review_text: Worst almond milk latte ever. Foam was herrendous and the pour wasn’t even a pour. If I wanted over heatwd almond milk with weak esspresso, I would make it at home. Waist or $7. Wish I could have gotten a refund. Sorry, I don’t like to do negative reviews but this one was bad.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Kelly, I’m sorry to hear that your experience at our cafe wasn’t satisfactory. I’m not exactly sure what happened with your drink and I apologize for the poor quality. We would have happily made it again or made you an entirely different drink if you preferred. We always want our customers to always leave happy and satisfied with their purchase.

reviews_data.review_text: Largest location I've been too including fun outdoor seating.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Alessandra, thank you for taking the time to write such a great review. I hope your drink and service was excellent. Thanks again.

reviews_data.review_text: Blueberry Foam + Latte = 10/10

reviews_data.review_text: Parking is hit or miss, but the inside space is clean, airy, with booths and tables perfect for working. Tried the banana pudding latte it was great. Will be back!

reviews_data.review_text: The food is great, the coffee is exceptional, and the staff is very pleasant. The atmosphere is absolutely perfect whether you’re working remotely or reconnecting with friends and colleagues, I can think of no better place to visit or start your day off with.

Only downsides are parking and food selection could be more filled.

reviews_data.review_text: Some of the other Summit locations are my favorite coffee shops in Charlotte. This location doesn't even compare. Occasionally I would get a decent drink if there was a good barista working there, but that was rare, and turnover is so high there's almost no chance you'll see the same person twice. It's clear that the training is basically non-existent for new hires. There are so many signs that the management/owners are incompetent and I won't be back unless someone else takes over.
Good coffee with a nice seating area to do your thing.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Dat, I love your review, particularly because we have so many people here just doing there thing. Whether you’re working, socializing with friends or family or just relaxing with some headphones. We are here so people can do their thing.

reviews_data.review_text: I truly love the Charlotte coffee scene. I now have been to over12 coffee shops all were very chic and modern. This place did not disappoint. I got the Salted Caramel Espresso Latte with almond milk which was delicious. This is local chain in Charlotte. I think they have about 6 locations. The prices are average for the area. Definitely will be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Kara, 
We are lucky that Charlotte has so many amazing coffee shops. I’m glad you had the opportunity to visit Summit Coffee Eastover and had an enjoyable experience. I hope you come back soon so we have the opportunity to bring your rating to a 5 star. I hope you have a wonderful week and thank you for taking time to share your thoughts with us.

reviews_data.review_text: The iced matcha & great indoor seating options at this location got me through many grad school papers! Loved studying from here. The staff is super friendly, the place is clean and I love getting points for free drinks on the app! Parking space is limited at this location, but so far the parallel street parking across from the coffee shop is still available to use. Hope it stays that way! Love this coffee shop!!

Good luck and please stop by to see us soon.

Friend recommended this coffee place!
Probably my next fav place to go and just hangout .

Since the day we opened we have been a go to place to hangout out with friends, family and business acquaintances. We appreciate you taking time out of your day to write us a review. reviews_data.review_text:
If you are looking for a coffee spot that combines exceptional quality with a welcoming atmosphere, Summit Coffee Eastover is a gem you do not want to miss. From the moment you walk in, the cozy ambiance and friendly staff make you feel right at home.

Each cup is crafted with care, whether you are indulging in a perfectly brewed espresso or savoring one of their signature lattes. The baristas are knowledgeable and genuinely passionate about coffee, which is evident in every sip.

Beyond the coffee, the Eastover location stands out with its inviting decor and comfortable seating. It is an ideal spot for catching up with friends, studying, or simply enjoying a moment of relaxation. The menu also features a variety of delicious pastries that pair perfectly with their beverages.

Summit Coffee Eastover excels in delivering a top-notch coffee experience, and it is clear they prioritize both quality and customer satisfaction. If you have not visited yet, do yourself a favor and check it out - you will not be disappointed!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Anthony, Thank you for the most thoughtful detailed review ever. We are happy you enjoy our cafe and all we have to offer. We don't take for granted the amazing customers we have and we are always trying to get a tiny bit better everyday. Thanks again for coming in and taking time to write this awesome review.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee and staff were awesome!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Dylan, it really means a lot to us to hear your positive feedback regarding our staff and coffee. Our staff really tries to make every effort to make our customers happy, and Summit Coffee’s coffee program is first class. Thanks for the review, we appreciate you and hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
Lots of indoor seating
Drinks were bland and lacking flavor.
Definitely aesthetic appeal over anything on the menu.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Arlene, I’m sorry you didn’t love your drink. We are always happy to make you and any other customer a new drink, either the same or something else if you prefer. Our first priority is to make sure our customers are satisfied. We would have loved the chance to make it right.

reviews_data.review_text:
We were consistent customers who loved going here, but we’re given attitude by the two closers (especially the male, very unprofessional) on Friday, September 6th when we tried to order a matcha an hour before closing because you guys began your closing process at 5:30, when the espresso machine isn’t even needed for a matcha. Make it make sense!!!!!

For everyone wondering, they close at 7 on Friday’s and denied us service at 6:00 as we watched them begin their closing process at 5:30.
reviews_data.owner_answer: I'm sorry you had a bad experience at our cafe, I will discuss this issue with the baristas. However, we do close at 6:00pm on Fridays, not 7:00pm. Closing our cafe is a bit of a lengthy process so we actually encourage the baristas to start the process early as long as it doesn't interfere with our customers. Our policy is not to kick people out of the cafe once we close but unfortunately we have to draw the line on food and beverage service.  I will make sure our business hours are more clearly posted.

reviews_data.review_text:
I’m a coffee lover, and the coffee here is amazing. I always order a latte with almond milk and it always taste really good. The place itself is very pleasant and peaceful.
Also, the croissants here are insane. I would definitely recommend this place 100%
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Judith, We appreciate your review and love that you found some cafe favorites. Our Croissants come from the summit bakery, we also make our scones in house. Thanks again for the kind review. We hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Summit Eastover is one of my favorite coffee shops in Charlotte! The staff goes above and beyond in customer service and cafe quality! They are a fantastic location to work from, socialize, or simply order ahead for takeout! The parking is also super easy with the designated lot as well as plenty of street parking.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Ruth, Thank you for the incredible review. It really means a lot to us when a customer takes there valuable time to write an honest review. reviews_data.review_text: The coffee was so good that I started searching all the locations I could visit during a vacation to NC! Just delicious, no if, ands, or buts about it. Also, the big bun?! Literally sooooo tasty! I’ll absolutely be back during future visits!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Felicia,
Thank you for visiting our cafe and leaving a very kind review. I'm glad you loved the coffee and the big bun. Our coffee is sourced from multiple regions and roasted locally by the Summit Coffee Roastery. Many of the farms are women owned. We really do spend a lot of time and effort to make sure we are serving not just great coffee, but also coffee with diverse and interesting flavor profiles. Our fresh pastries are homemade in house or provided by the Summit Bakery. Thanks again for your recent visit and we look forward to seeing you again in the future.

reviews_data.review_text:
I recently had the pleasure of hosting my spectacular 50th birthday celebration at Summit Coffee Eastover, surrounded by my family and friends. The venue’s expansive windows offered breathtaking views, creating a truly stunning atmosphere as the evening unfolded. The versatile seating options both inside and outside the shop were perfect for accommodating my large group of 50 guests. The space provided an ideal setup for a DJ, a designated area for dancing, a Photo Booth, and even room for catered BBQ meal, complete with a selection of wine and beer at counter.

The service provided by Summit Coffee was exceptional, and the owners went above and beyond to ensure everything ran smoothly. Their accommodating nature and abundance of fantastic ideas added an extra layer of magic to the event. If you are in search of the perfect venue for your next gathering, I wholeheartedly recommend considering Summit Coffee- it exceeded all of my expectations.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Patricia, Happy Birthday🎂 I worked during your party and everyone was having a blast. Not many people realize we do catering and also rent our space out for parties, social groups, and other events. I'm happy we were able to accommodate your group, the DJ and Photo booth were big hits. You also brought in you most of your own food and set up a buffet on the bar which is a good way to save some money. We appreciate the incredible review, Thank you so much for taking the time to write about your experience with us.

Thank you for sharing your experience with us, it really means a lot to a small business.

There is plenty of seating for us to gather and hangout while we chat. I see a lot of regulars who come in for a coffee and do some work. Definitely a great place to meet a friend and hangout if you are ever interested.

I also plan to share this review with our baristas who always do there best to represent our cafe with dedication, hard work and plenty of smiles for our customers. We are a true community cafe and we absolutely love where we are and the people we serve. reviews_data.review_text:
This location was, in a word, meh.
The parking lot was full at 3:45pm on a Wednesday. Street parking is sometimes available (pay attention to towing zone signs), but the parking situation was frustrating at best and definitely put a damper on my experience.
Once I found a place to park, I walked in to the calming, familiar teal interior of the café. Baristas were… not my favorite. They weren’t explicitly rude, but very cold and seemed annoyed at me questioning the menu. Asked if any sweets were dairy free, barista just shrugged. That’s okay—they weren’t marked, I didn’t expect barista to know but a verbal response would have been appreciated.
However, the biggest reason for the three stars is that NONE of the cold foam drinks can be made dairy-free. In 2023, it is ridiculous that they REFUSE to do this, even Sbux can do it for some drinks! I didn’t even bother asking them to use sanitized equipment for my drink after hearing this. I got the (seasonal, I think) lavender honey latte, but did not enjoy the charge for DF milk, as other Summit locations don’t have this.
All in all, the Plaza location is only 10 minutes away and far better than this one.
